==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cosinage
<hw>Cos"in*age</hw> <pr>(k?s"'n-?j)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Cousinage</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Collateral
relationship or kindred by blood; consanguinity.</def> <au>Burrill.</au>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A writ to recover possession of an estate in lands,
when a stranger has entered, after the death of the grandfather's
grandfather, or other distant collateral relation.</def>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

